, "b": "oil", "w": 2}, {"a": "com", "b": "eft", "w": 2}, {"a": "ai", "b": "bigoil", "w": 1}, {"a": "ai", "b": "lng", "w": 1}, {"a": "bigoil", "b": "lng", "w": 1}, {"a": "bigoil", "b": "oilandgas", "w": 1}, {"a": "lng", "b": "oilandgas", "w": 1}, {"a": "crude", "b": "elliottwave", "w": 1}, {"a": "crude", "b": "oil", "w": 1}, {"a": "dubai", "b": "oil", "w": 1}, {"a": "oil", "b": "wti", "w": 1}, {"a": "china", "b": "market", "w": 1}, {"a": "china", "b": "oilprices", "w": 1}, {"a": "market", "b": "oilprices", "w": 1}, {"a": "coaltwitter", "b": "lng", "w": 1}, {"a": "lng", "b": "natgas", "w": 1}, {"a": "hormuz", "b": "petróleo", "w": 1}, {"a": "hormuz", "b": "oil", "w": 1}, {"a": "natgas", "b": "ongt", "w": 1}]}, "top_tweets": [{"id": "2067483527789105317", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067483527789105317", "text": "Another Treaty of Versailles? \n\n(Surely someone at the White House knew that signing a MoU at Versailles that effectively gives Iran billions of dollars in oil money had some bad historical echoes? I bet the host — President Macron — knew it too well)", "time": "05:44", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 54570, "likes": 489, "replies": 43, "retweets": 97, "quotes": 12, "bookmarks": 27, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2067490403087974796", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067490403087974796", "text": "Oil prices are now DOWN year-on-year. \n\nWTI is trading at $74.5 a barrel. It was at $75 back on June 18, 2025 (during the Twelve-Day War between Israel and Iran, and US Operation Midnight Hammer). Still trading well above the most immediate pre-war levels in Feb 2026, when WTI was ~$60.", "time": "06:11", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 60040, "likes": 399, "replies": 34, "retweets": 74, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 30, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067502091627643105", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067502091627643105", "text": "The most common critique to my view that Beijing played a fundamental role in stabilizing the oil market says China’s oil imports simply fell along with imports by every other country in Asia because Hormuz was closed. I disagree. The critique appears to be based on  import data up to April, which m", "time": "06:58", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 112289, "likes": 427, "replies": 31, "retweets": 94, "quotes": 12, "bookmarks": 127, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand"]}}, {"id": "2067520066967556427", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067520066967556427", "text": "Saudi crude oil is on the move: 3 Saudi-owned VLCCs have re-appeared outside the Strait of Hormuz with about 6 million barrels.  NOTE: those are not yet a sign that Saudi is re-starting production, but rather moving crude loaded in late Feb / early Mar inside the Persian Gulf.", "time": "08:09", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 37168, "likes": 326, "replies": 6, "retweets": 78, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 26, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2067524786176000358", "url": "https://x.com/GregaHorvatFX/status/2067524786176000358", "text": "Crude extends nicely after the triangle breakdown. \n\nThe most important level will be 67/70.  \n\n#oil #OOTT  #crude #Elliottwave https://t.co/m6VratckGc", "time": "08:28", "author": "GregaHorvatFX", "author_name": "Grega Horvat", "followers": 36699, "views": 4927, "likes": 51, "replies": 9, "retweets": 9, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 13, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067527218780361017", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2067527218780361017", "text": "Confirmed Strait of Hormuz crossings continued on 17 June, with 6 verified transits recorded across the monitored zone. @Kpler #OOTT", "time": "08:37", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 48547, "likes": 173, "replies": 12, "retweets": 36, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067527848253116459", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2067527848253116459", "text": "Do you want to know what will spoil the deal?? THIS: Senior Israeli official: Despite the MOU, the IDF will not withdraw from southern Lebanon.  #OOTT", "time": "08:40", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 18187, "likes": 136, "replies": 14, "retweets": 26, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 2, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067565335528497623", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067565335528497623", "text": "\"... Taking into account the situation in the Middle East, we discussed reducing dependence on oil passing through the Strait of Hormuz...\"\n\n(Japan is moving to reduce its SoH dependency forever. note it says SoH rather than Persian Gulf, so bypass pipelines may play a role)", "time": "11:09", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 34776, "likes": 90, "replies": 6, "retweets": 26, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Demand outlook", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2067574823124123984", "url": "https://x.com/CRUDEOIL231/status/2067574823124123984", "text": "Shoutout to this beautiful peace. Dropping the SAR radar feed today on June 18th—we're seeing some vessel prints picking up east of the SoH. It’s nowhere near normal flow velocity, but at least five hulls are making way. Looks like they’re hugging the Iranian corridor.\n\n#oott #iran", "time": "11:47", "author": "CRUDEOIL231", "author_name": "JH", "followers": 59314, "views": 18490, "likes": 131, "replies": 8, "retweets": 9, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067595212864606356", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067595212864606356", "text": "CHART OF THE DAY: US gasoline average retail price drops below $4 per gallon for the first time since late March (to $3.999). \n\nGasoline remains expensive vs pre-war levels, but politically, the fact the first digit of the price is now a 3 is very important for Donald Trump. https://t.co/Gupm003Asz", "time": "13:08", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 27334, "likes": 185, "replies": 6, "retweets": 37, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Refining/products", "Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067601212250157392", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067601212250157392", "text": "MUST READ: Kuwait has started ramping up oil production and plans to reach 2 million b/d within a week (from 0.5m b/d during the war), KPC CEO Sheikh Nawaf Al-Sabah tells @FionamMacDonald in an interview. He says recovery faster than previously thought.\nhttps://t.co/RMethuGdgM", "time": "13:31", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 60447, "likes": 448, "replies": 21, "retweets": 126, "quotes": 10, "bookmarks": 51, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["OPEC+", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2067605700193271819", "url": "https://x.com/IliaBouchouev/status/2067605700193271819", "text": "Another massive binary option (Sep Brt $70 put) traded for 100 million barrels (!!!) in one go as a stark reminder of the hidden power of OTC oil markets.\nTheir pricing is highly sensitive to the shape of the vol skew (see more in the book/YouTube channel).\n#oott https://t.co/Qi3vaS1reY", "time": "13:49", "author": "IliaBouchouev", "author_name": "Dr. Ilia Bouchouev", "followers": 19952, "views": 8099, "likes": 30, "replies": 7, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2067634983410507979", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2067634983410507979", "text": "The risks behind the Iran-US breakthrough https://t.co/ZE8MPQOYcA #OOTT #US #IranWar‌", "time": "15:46", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 7342, "likes": 35, "replies": 3, "retweets": 15, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 7, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Geopolitics", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2067652817960014035", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2067652817960014035", "text": "Saudi Arabia has started moving a cluster of empty  (ballast) VLCC tankers it has kept near India for most of the conflict toward the Gulf of Oman for a potential Strait of Hormuz crossing. Another sign that oil production in the Persian Gulf is/will be coming back. https://t.co/BgrAzxxD46", "time": "16:57", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 34209, "likes": 408, "replies": 16, "retweets": 85, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 29, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2067710356344963261", "url": "https://x.com/pickeringenergy/status/2067710356344963261", "text": "Iran Video #14 - Obviously, tons happening. We cover what to watch (Strait traffic, restart timing, China demand, Iran shennanigans, inventory trends). Crude feels asymetric risk/reward in low/mid$70s..the next 60 days will feel like a year. #EFT #OOTT\n\nhttps://t.co/DnhfptAEd6", "time": "20:45", "author": "pickeringenergy", "author_name": "Dan Pickering", "followers": 36384, "views": 4022, "likes": 23, "replies": 9, "retweets": 8, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Prices/technicals"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 41, "views": 125957, "likes": 383}, {"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 14, "views": 455499, "likes": 2946}, {"username": "avionsunantiqu1", "name": "Nicholas James", "followers": 1433, "tweets": 12, "views": 12045, "likes": 98}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 8, "views": 13244, "likes": 40}, {"username": "Amena__Bakr", "name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "tweets": 4, "views": 85601, "likes": 446}], "top_authors_by_views": [{"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 14, "views": 455499, "likes": 2946}, {"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 41, "views": 125957, "likes": 383}, {"username": "Amena__Bakr", "name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "tweets": 4, "views": 85601, "likes": 446}, {"username": "CRUDEOIL231", "name": "JH", "followers": 59314, "tweets": 1, "views": 18490, "likes": 131}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 8, "views": 13244, "likes": 40}], "sentiment": {"price": {"labeled": 146, "relevant": 146, "pos